$$README.text:
Here's how to install Zil.

(0) Unload the PDS's (should be done by the time you're reading this).

(1) Edit the $$ZILSET member of this PDS.

(2) Edit and run (under ISPF) the $$CONFIG exec in the CLIST PDS.

(3) Edit and submit the INSTALL1 member of this PDS.

(4) Edit and submit the INSTALL2 member of this PDS.

(5) Edit and submit the ZILTEST  member of this PDS to verify install.

Bugs and praises to: seb@draper.com

$$ZILSET.text:
(eval-when (compile eval)
;
; Uncomment these lines and change the feature names to whatever.
; Duplicate as many times as you like, once for each feature.
; For example, you could use your company name.
; Case is not significant; symbols are stored as uppercase, though
; you could have a mixed-case symbol like '|BogusCom| if you wanted.
;
;   (set-feature   'my-feature-name)
;   (set-feature   'another-feature-name)
;
; Do not change these (unless you happen to have a vector facility).
;
    (set-nofeature 'draper)             ; Name of installation.
    (set-nofeature 'csdl)               ; Another installation.
    (set-nofeature 'vf)                 ; No vector facility.
)

//SEB1525Z JOB MSGCLASS=H,NOTIFY=SEB1525,TIME=(5,30)
//*
//* Test out all of ZIL using ZILTEST function.
//*
//* In other words, this verifies all examples in the Zil documentation.
//*
//* Must be done under TSO because of use of (TSO) function.
//*
//* ===============================================================
//*
//* It is normal for the output of this run to contain error messages
//* and warnings.  The only messages which indicate an unexpected
//* problem or discrepancy are those which look like this:
//*
//*  Wrong!!! Doc and implementation mismatch!
//*  The documentation says...
//*  The LISP system returns..
//*
//* These produce summary messages of the form:
//*
//*  There are <nnn> errors in your documentation or implementation.
//*
//* If you see any of these, please check to see that you have
//* configured your system properly, or report them as a bug.
//*
//* ===============================================================
//*
//* Most of the data set names are changed by the $$CONFIG exec.  But
//* you may edit JOB or EXEC parameters yourself.
//*
//* ===============================================================
//*
//ZILTEST  EXEC PGM=IKJEFT01,DYNAMNBR=150
//SYSTSPRT DD   SYSOUT=*
//ZILO     DD   SYSOUT=*
//ZILDRIBL DD   SYSOUT=*
